AMI update is recommended after significant changes in mitf docker image

To update image routing-mapdata-rd (108215386062) account should be used ( contact @yaremenk if you need support )

Switch to the corresponding profile:

export AWS_PROFILE=routing-mapdata-rd

Inject DOCKER_IMAGE as env variable:

. ../docker.cfg
DOCKER_REGISTRY=docker-local.artifactory.in.here.com/cci
export DOCKER_IMAGE=$DOCKER_REGISTRY/$DOCKER_IMAGE_NAME

Run packer:

packer build packer-ec2.json


Copy ami id from the output:
--> amazon-ebs: AMIs were created:
us-east-1: ami-id-here

Update AMI ID in jenkins configuration https://ivi-mitf.jenkins.release.in.here.com/configure

Remove old AMI.
